==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pediment
<hw>Ped"i*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>pes</ets>,
<ets>pedis</ets>, a foot. See <er>Foot</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>Originally, in classical architecture, the triangular space forming
the gable of a simple roof; hence, a similar form used as a decoration
over porticoes, doors, windows, etc.; also, a rounded or broken frontal
having a similar position and use. See <er>Temple</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pedimental</ent>⟦br⟧
